text: Na Kyung-won (, born 6 December 1963) is a South Korean judge and politician. She is a member of the conservative People Power Party. She has been a member of the National Assembly since 2004. From December 2018 to December 2019 she was the parliamentary leader of the Liberty Korea Party, the first woman to hold the position. In April 2025, Na declared her candidacy for President of South Korea in the 2025 snap presidential election. She lost in the primaries held by the People Power Party. ==References== ==Other websites== * Official website Category:1963 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Seoul Category:South Korean lawyers
